To check transaction log file usage for each database
dbcc sqlperf(logspace)

The purpose of DBCC checkdb

The primary purpose is to check both the logical and physical intergrity of all objects in the specified database.
It is a resource intensive opertion and should be executed during off hours and with specific options for large databases

Complete systax of DBCC checkdb
DBCC CHECKDB
 ('database_name', [,NOINDEX | {REPAIR_ALLOW_DATA_LOSS|REPAIR_FAST|REPAIR_REBUILD} ] ) [WITH {[ALL_ERRORMSGS]
[,[NO_INFOMSGS]][,[TABLOCK]][,[ESTIMATE_ONLY]][,[PHYSICAL_ONLY]]}]

DBCC CHECKDB SYNTAX OPTIONS

--CHECKS ALL DATA IN DATABASE --8 SECONDS
DBCC CHECKDB('PROD12')

-- SPECIFIES THE NON-CLUSTERED INDEXES FOR NON SYSTEM DATABASES NOT TO BE CHECKED
DBCC CHECKDB('PROD12', NOINDEX) --5 SECONDS

--SUPPRESSESS ALL INFORMATION MESSAGES (USE IN A LARGE DATABASE)
USE PROD12
GO
DBCC CHECKDB WITH NO_INFOMSGS  <<- PROVIDES NO DATA EXCEPT TO INDICATE THAT THE DBCC WAS SUCCESSFUL

--DISPLAYS THE ESTIMATED AMOUNT OF TEMPDB NEEDED, TO UNLOAD INTEGRITY CHECK TO THE TEMPDB)
DBCC CHECKDB ('TEMPDB') WITH ESTIMATEONLY

--THIS CHECKS PHYSICAL ON-DISK STRUCTURES, BUT OMITS THE INTERNAL LOGICAL CHECKS
DBCC CHECKDB ('PROD12') WITH PHYSICAL_ONLY

--IN PRODUCTION ONLY OPTION WE USE IS LOGTOTABLE=Y AND EXTENDEDLOGICALCHECKS=N




